cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY

This paper deals with security vulnerabilities in computing systems, specifically Spectre attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves program transformations, which falls under cs.AR (Architecture), and code modifications, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a prototype system, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering), and the evaluation of performance overhead, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
